subject: Figure Skating
lead_paragraph: Kim Yu-Na of South Korea captured the Skate America women’s title in Everett, Wash., winning the free skate and short program. It was a disappointing debut for the former world champion Kimmie Meissner, the 2007 Skate America winner. Meissner, who switched coaches in February, was eighth over all.
